Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of operations to make n equal to 0. We can use the bitwise AND operation to achieve this. The algorithm works by repeatedly performing the bitwise AND operation between n and (n - 1), which effectively removes the least significant bit of n. This process continues until n becomes 0. The time complexity is O(log(n)) due to the iterative process of removing the least significant bit. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single variable to store the result. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs bitwise operations, which are computationally efficient.

